    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-09-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-09-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="365" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d365">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Clay</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 222.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-09-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 24, 1866.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 30th of August,
                            without number (No. 117,) has been received.</p>
                <p>The President is gratified to learn that Assistant Secretary Fox has
                            performed his work in so acceptable a manner with regard to the special
                            mission with which he was intrusted near the person of the Emperor of
                            Russia. When full details of that transaction shall have been received
                            here, I shall have occasion to advert to the subject again.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cassius M. Clay,</hi> Esq<hi rend="italic">.,
                                    &amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
